<div type="definition">
<p>SECRET INVESTIGATION of the SITUATION in OTHER STATES.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for spying is jiàn 間, and this is the general word for military intelligence used in SUN.</p>
<p>2. Dié 諜 refers to strictly professional and government-sponsored spying of any kind.</p>
<p>3. Tàn 探 refers to a spy-like operation which is not necessarily entirely secret.</p>
<p>4. Hòu 候 refers specifically to military espionage on the borders.</p>
        </div>
